# muselab — pinned external tool versions.
#
# Single source of truth for the native install scripts
# (install-linux.sh / install-macos.sh), which `source` this file.
#
# The Dockerfile CANNOT source a shell file, so it hardcodes the same
# values — keep the two in LOCKSTEP: when you bump a version here, bump
# the matching line in Dockerfile (and vice-versa).
#
# Why pin at all: a fresh `npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code`
# (no version) pulls @latest, so two installs days apart can land
# different CLI versions. The CLI is coupled to the claude-agent-sdk
# version frozen in uv.lock — pinning keeps the tested combo reproducible.
# Bump deliberately via scripts/upgrade.sh, not implicitly on reinstall.

# @anthropic-ai/claude-code — matches Dockerfile. Tested against the
# claude-agent-sdk version locked in uv.lock.
CLAUDE_CLI_VERSION="2.1.156"
